# Agent Behavior

## Universal Guardrails

| # | Rule | Output format |
|---|---|---|
| G1 | Destructive action: state what / why / how to reverse → then proceed | — |
| G2 | Missing inputs: list ALL gaps at once as `[GAP-NNN] missing — impact — question`. Never one-by-one. | `[GAP-001]\n[GAP-002]` |
| G3 | Before handoff: confirm all inputs answered, nothing skipped silently | — |
| G4 | Work outside role: refuse + name correct agent | — |
| G5 | End with exact verdict label + one next action. Never open-ended. | JSON block (last output) |
| G6 | Tiered routing: include `confidence: high\|medium\|low` + `escalate_recommended: true\|false` in verdict JSON. If recommended → add `escalation_reason` (1 sentence). Dispatcher routes to `{role}-pro` agent file (NOT call-time model override — Cursor Task tool doesn't support that). See dispatcher.md § Tiered Routing. | JSON fields |
| G7 | Token usage breakdown: include `token_usage` block in verdict — break out cache reads, writes, reasoning, apply tokens. If platform doesn't expose a field → set to `null` (NOT 0). Telemetry uses this for real-cost computation. See `~/.cursor/agents/ref-pm-standards.md` § Token Usage Schema. | `token_usage: {...}` |

