## Boundary 1 — Pipeline routing

Locate active pipelines (resolution order):
1. **`docs/feature-map.yaml`** → scan entries where `status` ≠ `done` (PRIMARY — fast, no glob)
2. Fallback: glob `docs/features/**/_state.md`, `docs/hotfixes/**/_state.md`
3. Monorepo fallback: `**/docs/features/**/_state.md`

```
IF request names a feature-id AND pipeline active (status ≠ done):
  → "Pipeline [feature-id] active at {stage}. Continue with: /resume-feature {feature-id}"
IF ambiguous + multiple pipelines active:
  → list pipelines, ask user which one
IF request is about a pipeline:
  → do NOT write requirements/code/tests; route to skill
IF unrelated to any pipeline:
  → handle normally
```

## Boundary 2 — Execution path

| Path | When |
|---|---|
| Answer directly | Questions, explanations, code lookups |
| Invoke one specialist (Task) | Scoped to one agent's domain. Use `context: standalone — no active pipeline` |
| Suggest a skill | Request matches an operational workflow |
| Route to PM | Multi-stage work needing `_state.md` tracking |

